benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/search - Search custom fields by type, name and optional value

covered: Valid Request: Core success paths covered (TC01) and broad parameter combinations (TC02-TC06, TC12, TC37).
Empty Response: Handling when no data is available (TC11, TC28).
Pagination: Tests covering limit/offset and large datasets (TC07, TC21, TC22) and performance-related timing (TC30, TC31).
Query Parameters: Comprehensive coverage across objectType, fieldName, fieldValue, and handling of extra/invalid parameters (TC02-06, TC12, TC37).
Security: SQL injection (TC19) and XSS (TC20) scenarios.
Audit/Dependency Integration: FULL/MINIMAL/NONE audit handling (TC08-10) and audit service availability/degradation (TC18, TC33), plus data consistency (TC32).
State Variation: Empty and partially populated databases (TC28, TC29).
Backward compatibility: Legacy client using only objectType (TC27).
Performance: Normal and peak load timing tests (TC30, TC31).
Regression: FieldName and FULL audit regression checks (TC25-26).
Integration: Data consistency with audit log service (TC32).
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or rate limiting behavior under high request volume.
Caching Behavior: No tests covering caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache validation.
Authorization: No explicit test for 403/insufficient-permissions scenarios.
Server Error Handling: No explicit tests for 500 Internal Server Error scenarios beyond audit-service unavailability (e.g., DB outages).
recommendations: Add tests for rate limiting/throttling behavior (e.g., 429 responses).
Add tests asserting caching headers presence and behavior (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache reuse/validation.
Add explicit 403/insufficient-permissions tests to complement 401 missing-auth tests.
Add tests covering 500 Internal Server Error scenarios (e.g., database failure).
Document and validate consistent error codes/messages across invalid inputs and audit-related failures.
